For some reason I don't trust the obvious answer, so please reply to me
and I'll summarize.

I've got a host that is on two networks.  Do I give it two names?  If
not, then how do I solve this problem:  I'm running on that host, and
I want to do a broadcast on the first network.  Or I'm on a different
host and I want to set up the "most efficient" TCP link between it and
me -- the multi-homed host does no gateway work.

Thanks.
	/r$
-- 
